<tr box="[167,1424,818,1135]" gridrow="1" pageId="13" pageNumber="236">
<th box="[167,289,818,1135]" gridcol="0" gridrow="1" pageId="13" pageNumber="236">punctation in posterior longitudinal furrow of pronotum</th>
<td box="[318,548,818,1135]" gridcol="1" gridrow="1" pageId="13" pageNumber="236">punctation very dense; punctures very large, diameter of largest of them in transversal view larger than width of fourth transverse ridge; there is no area without punctation</td>
<td box="[573,827,818,1135]" gridcol="2" gridrow="1" pageId="13" pageNumber="236">punctation very dense; punctures moderately size, diameter of largest of them in transversal view smaller than width of fourth transverse ridge; there is no area without punctation</td>
<td box="[851,1122,818,1135]" gridcol="3" gridrow="1" pageId="13" pageNumber="236">punctation very dense; punctures moderately large, diameter of largest of them in transversal view smaller than width of fourth transverse ridge; there is no area without punctation</td>
<td box="[1147,1424,818,1135]" gridcol="4" gridrow="1" pageId="13" pageNumber="236">punctation very dense; punctures large, diameter of largest of them in transversal view much smaller than width of fourth transverse ridge; in anterior part of posteriori longitudinal furrow there is small longitudinal surface without punctation</td>
</tr>
<tr box="[167,1424,1151,1293]" gridrow="2" pageId="13" pageNumber="236">
<th box="[167,289,1151,1293]" gridcol="0" gridrow="2" pageId="13" pageNumber="236">structure of transversal ridges of pronotum</th>
<td box="[318,548,1151,1293]" gridcol="1" gridrow="2" pageId="13" pageNumber="236">very low, weakly visible, arranged in clearly regular, broadly interrupted transverse structures</td>
<td box="[573,827,1151,1293]" gridcol="2" gridrow="2" pageId="13" pageNumber="236">low but clearly visible, arranged in regular, cointinous, transverse structures</td>
<td box="[851,1122,1151,1293]" gridcol="3" gridrow="2" pageId="13" pageNumber="236">low but clearly visible, arranged in irregular transverse structures</td>
<td box="[1147,1424,1151,1293]" gridcol="4" gridrow="2" pageId="13" pageNumber="236">clearly convex, clearly visible, arranged in regular transverse structures; ridges 1 and 2 continuous, others interrupted</td>
</tr>
<tr box="[167,1424,1309,1392]" gridrow="3" pageId="13" pageNumber="236">
<th box="[167,289,1309,1392]" gridcol="0" gridrow="3" pageId="13" pageNumber="236">sides of pronotum</th>
<td box="[318,548,1309,1392]" gridcol="1" gridrow="3" pageId="13" pageNumber="236">distinctly rounded, very slightly sinuate before hind angles</td>
<td box="[573,827,1309,1392]" gridcol="2" gridrow="3" pageId="13" pageNumber="236">distinctly rounded, slightly sinuate before hind angles</td>
<td box="[851,1122,1309,1392]" gridcol="3" gridrow="3" pageId="13" pageNumber="236">distinctly rounded, distinctly sinuate before hind angles</td>
<td box="[1147,1424,1309,1392]" gridcol="4" gridrow="3" pageId="13" pageNumber="236">less distinctly rounded, slightly sinuate before hind angles</td>
</tr>
<tr box="[167,1424,1408,1549]" gridrow="4" pageId="13" pageNumber="236">
<th box="[167,289,1408,1549]" gridcol="0" gridrow="4" pageId="13" pageNumber="236">macrosetae on border of sides and base of pronotum</th>
<td box="[318,548,1408,1549]" gridcol="1" gridrow="4" pageId="13" pageNumber="236">druseform, with jagged edges</td>
<td box="[573,827,1408,1549]" gridcol="2" gridrow="4" pageId="13" pageNumber="236">clubbed, with edges with a regular structure</td>
<td box="[851,1122,1408,1549]" gridcol="3" gridrow="4" pageId="13" pageNumber="236">clubbed, with edges with a regular structure</td>
<td box="[1147,1424,1408,1549]" gridcol="4" gridrow="4" pageId="13" pageNumber="236">clubbed, with edges with a regular structure</td>
</tr>
<tr box="[167,1424,1565,1677]" gridrow="5" pageId="13" pageNumber="236">
<th box="[167,289,1565,1677]" gridcol="0" gridrow="5" pageId="13" pageNumber="236">humeral denticles</th>
<td box="[318,548,1565,1677]" gridcol="1" gridrow="5" pageId="13" pageNumber="236">distinctly developed, but less distinct from others</td>
<td box="[573,827,1565,1677]" gridcol="2" gridrow="5" pageId="13" pageNumber="236">distinctly developed, more distinct from others</td>
<td box="[851,1122,1565,1677]" gridcol="3" gridrow="5" pageId="13" pageNumber="236">distinctly developed, more distinct from others</td>
<td box="[1147,1424,1565,1677]" gridcol="4" gridrow="5" pageId="13" pageNumber="236">distinctly developed, more distinct from others</td>
</tr>
<tr box="[167,1424,1694,1776]" gridrow="6" pageId="13" pageNumber="236">
<th box="[167,289,1694,1776]" gridcol="0" gridrow="6" pageId="13" pageNumber="236">elytra</th>
<td box="[318,548,1694,1776]" gridcol="1" gridrow="6" pageId="13" pageNumber="236">paralel, with less distinct tubercles on intervals</td>
<td box="[573,827,1694,1776]" gridcol="2" gridrow="6" pageId="13" pageNumber="236">paralel, with more distinct tubercles on intervals</td>
<td box="[851,1122,1694,1776]" gridcol="3" gridrow="6" pageId="13" pageNumber="236">paralel, with more distinct tubercles on intervals</td>
<td box="[1147,1424,1694,1776]" gridcol="4" gridrow="6" pageId="13" pageNumber="236">weakly widened in the middle, with more distinct tubercles on intervals</td>
</tr>
</table>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1436,1824,1958]" pageId="13" pageNumber="236">
It is interesting is that, on the border of sides and base of pronotum newly described species has characteristic druseform macrosetae (
<figureCitation box="[417,502,1860,1887]" captionStart="FIGURES 30–35" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1357,1381]" captionTargetBox="[169,1424,194,1323]" captionTargetId="figure-18@14.[151,1436,181,1334]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 30–35. Details of the morphology. 30–32, Agrilinus matusiaki Minkina, new species, holotype, male: 30, aedeagus, lateral view; 31, aedeagus, dorsal view; 32, epipharynx.33, Gilletianus miurai Minkina, new species, holotype,male, epipharynx; 34, Trichiorhyssemus immaturus Minkina, new species, holotype, female, epipharynx; 35, T. immaturus Minkina, new species, holotype, female, druseform macrosetae on border of pronotum." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6810134" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6810134/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="236">Fig. 35</figureCitation>
). This shape of macrosetae was not observed in any known 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Clouet" authorityYear="1901" box="[1190,1387,1860,1886]" class="Insecta" family="Aphodiidae" genus="Trichiorhyssemus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="236" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1190,1387,1860,1886]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="236">Trichiorhyssemus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rakovic &amp; Kral" authorityYear="1997" box="[151,387,1896,1922]" class="Insecta" family="Aphodiidae" genus="Neotrichiorhyssemus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="236" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,387,1896,1922]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="236">Neotrichiorhyssemus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but may it be overlooked. Somewhat similar macrosetae was reported by 
<bibRefCitation author="Rakovic, M. &amp; Kral, D." pageId="13" pageNumber="236" pagination="233 - 247" refId="ref9112" refString="Rakovic, M. &amp; Kral, D. (1997) New taxa, new combinations and current taxonomic status of tribes and genera of Psammodiinae (Coleoptera: Scarabaeoidea: Aphodiidae). Acta Societatis Zoologicae Bohemicae, 61 (3), 233 - 247." type="journal article" year="1997">Rakovič &amp; Král (1997)</bibRefCitation>
in the genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Rakovic &amp; Kral, 1997" authorityName="Rakovic &amp; Kral" authorityYear="1997" box="[375,753,1932,1958]" class="Insecta" family="Aphodiidae" genus="Messyrhus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="236" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[375,494,1932,1958]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="236">Messyrhus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Rakovic, M. &amp; Kral, D." box="[501,753,1932,1958]" pageId="13" pageNumber="236" pagination="233 - 247" refId="ref9112" refString="Rakovic, M. &amp; Kral, D. (1997) New taxa, new combinations and current taxonomic status of tribes and genera of Psammodiinae (Coleoptera: Scarabaeoidea: Aphodiidae). Acta Societatis Zoologicae Bohemicae, 61 (3), 233 - 247." type="journal article" year="1997">Rakovič &amp; Král, 1997</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
